1. access and use the Covered Material for any purpose;
2. reproduce and make copies of the Covered Material;
3. install, execute, run, study, inspect, and analyze the Covered Material;
4. modify, adapt, translate, annotate, and transform the Covered Material;
5. create derivative works;
6. combine, link, embed, or integrate the Covered Material with other material;
7. compile and distribute source or object forms;
8. publish, display, perform, communicate, and make the Covered Material available;
9. distribute, sublicense, rent, lease, sell, and commercialize the Covered Material and derivative works;
10. provide products and services using the Covered Material;
11. conduct Machine-Learning Activity;
12. create, distribute, and use Derived Training Material; and
13. authorize another Eligible Person to perform any of these activities.

This grant permits commercial, non-commercial, academic, governmental, scientific, medical, military, security, research, educational, artistic, personal, and machine-learning uses.

No royalty, source-availability obligation, network-copyleft obligation, field-of-use restriction, ethical-use restriction, revenue limitation, user-count limitation, commercial-use limitation, or machine-learning restriction applies to an Eligible Person.

### 2.1 Artificial-Intelligence Freedom for Eligible Persons

Eligible Persons may freely use the Covered Material and Derived Training Material to train, evaluate, operate, improve, or provide artificial-intelligence systems.

As to Eligible Persons, the Licensor does not claim that a model, model weight, adapter, embedding model, generated output, or dataset becomes a derivative work of the Covered Material merely because the Covered Material was lawfully used in training or evaluation.

This paragraph does not disclaim any copyright that may independently subsist in a work containing recognizable or protectable expression copied from the Covered Material.

### 2.2 Database Rights

To the extent that a Licensor possesses database rights or similar extraction and reutilization rights in the Covered Material, the Licensor grants every Eligible Person the right to extract, reutilize, reproduce, adapt, analyze, mine, and distribute all or any portion of the relevant database.

### 2.3 Patent Grant

Each Licensor grants every Eligible Person a worldwide, royalty-free, fully paid-up, perpetual, irrevocable except as expressly provided by this License, non-exclusive patent license under patent claims owned or controlled by that Licensor that are necessarily infringed by the unmodified Covered Material or its authorized use.

No patent license is granted for claims infringed only because of an Eligible Person’s independent modifications or combinations.

If an Eligible Person institutes patent litigation alleging that the Covered Material directly or contributorily infringes a patent, the patent license granted to that person under this section terminates as of the date the litigation is filed.

### 2.4 Moral Rights

To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, each Licensor waives and agrees not to assert moral rights against an Eligible Person’s authorized exercise of this License.

