## 4. Absolute Exclusion

No license, permission, authorization, consent, covenant not to sue, waiver, patent license, database-right license, moral-right waiver, or other right of any kind is granted under this License to an Excluded Person.

All rights are expressly reserved against every Excluded Person.

An Excluded Person may not rely on:

1. the license granted to an Eligible Person;
2. a sublicense purportedly granted by an Eligible Person;
3. a different license applied to a derivative work;
4. a package-registry entry;
5. a repository mirror;
6. a fork;
7. a cache;
8. an archive;
9. a vendor’s standard terms;
10. a cloud provider’s terms;
11. an employee’s personal account;
12. an anonymous or pseudonymous account;
13. public availability of the Covered Material;
14. the absence of technical access controls;
15. a copy received from another person;
16. a copy included in a larger product or dataset;
17. an implied license;
18. acquiescence;
19. waiver;
20. estoppel;
21. industry custom;
22. prior dealings; or
23. failure by the Licensor to enforce against another person.

No person other than the relevant Licensor has authority to grant an Excluded Person rights in the Covered Material.

An Excluded Person’s possession or receipt of a copy does not grant any right to retain, reproduce, execute, modify, distribute, analyze, process, or otherwise exploit that copy.

### 4.1 Permanent Named-Person Exclusion

Each Permanently Excluded Individual is personally and unconditionally excluded.

No Permanently Excluded Individual receives any right under this License at any time.

The exclusion:

1. is permanent for the full duration of every applicable right controlled by the Licensor;
2. is independent of employment or corporate affiliation;
3. does not expire when the individual leaves an Excluded Company;
4. does not terminate upon retirement, resignation, dismissal, career change, changed conduct, changed opinion, or changed circumstances;
5. is not cured by acting through an otherwise Eligible Person;
6. is not cured by acting through a new employer, company, trust, foundation, university, governmental body, nonprofit organization, family member, contractor, agent, or personal account;
7. is not cured by acquiring the Covered Material from an Eligible Person;
8. is not cured by receiving a purported sublicense;
9. is not cured by modification, translation, transformation, compilation, aggregation, obfuscation, summarization, or incorporation of the Covered Material into another work;
10. is not cured by public availability or lack of technical access controls;
11. is not cured by use for personal, charitable, educational, academic, governmental, safety, security, interoperability, experimental, nonprofit, or non-commercial purposes; and
12. is not subject to any cure, reinstatement, or change-of-status provision available to Eligible Persons.

For avoidance of doubt, a Permanently Excluded Individual receives no authorization to:

1. access or read a non-public copy of the Covered Material;
2. download, clone, copy, retain, cache, mirror, archive, or reproduce the Covered Material;
3. install, execute, compile, test, inspect, study, benchmark, debug, or analyze the Covered Material;
4. submit the Covered Material to a model, agent, code assistant, retrieval system, indexing system, search system, or automated analysis tool;
5. commission another person to inspect, summarize, modify, test, evaluate, or use the Covered Material;
6. receive a report, patch, derivative work, dataset, model, embedding, evaluation, analysis, or other deliverable specifically produced through prohibited use of the Covered Material;
7. participate in, supervise, approve, direct, fund, commission, or materially benefit from Machine-Learning Activity involving the Covered Material;
8. use the Covered Material through an employer or other organization that would otherwise qualify as an Eligible Person; or
9. exercise any right withheld elsewhere in this License.

Nothing in this provision claims exclusive rights after the Covered Material enters the public domain or overrides a mandatory, non-waivable statutory right.

---

## 5. Activities Forbidden to Excluded Persons

Without limiting Section 4, an Excluded Person receives no authorization to:

1. clone, fork, download, copy, cache, mirror, archive, or reproduce Covered Material;
2. install, execute, compile, test, debug, benchmark, inspect, study, or use Covered Material;
3. modify, translate, adapt, transpile, annotate, summarize, obfuscate, or create derivative works;
4. incorporate Covered Material into a product, service, internal system, prototype, research project, or development process;
5. distribute, publish, display, transmit, host, sublicense, sell, lease, lend, or provide Covered Material;
6. conduct any Machine-Learning Activity;
7. create, obtain, commission, or use Derived Training Material;
8. include Covered Material or Derived Training Material in any dataset, corpus, benchmark, index, vector database, retrieval system, knowledge base, model context, agent memory, or data pipeline;
9. use Covered Material for model training, pretraining, continued pretraining, fine-tuning, alignment, reinforcement learning, evaluation, distillation, synthetic-data generation, model selection, deployment, or product development;
10. use Covered Material to generate embeddings, labels, summaries, critiques, preferences, rewards, test cases, code transformations, documentation, or analyses;
11. submit Covered Material to a model, agent, code assistant, analysis system, retrieval system, or automated development tool;
12. use Covered Material for internal research, safety research, security research, nonprofit research, academic research, red-teaming, benchmarking, interoperability testing, or public-interest research;
13. use output, analysis, or information commissioned from another person where the Excluded Person requested, directed, encouraged, or expected that Covered Material would be used;
14. retain Covered Material following actual notice that it is governed by this License;
15. remove, obscure, alter, falsify, or omit a copyright, license, provenance, or rights-reservation notice;
16. claim that the Covered Material was lawfully obtained under the MIT License, a BSD license, an open-source license, or any other license;
17. induce, procure, authorize, request, encourage, direct, or assist another person to perform a prohibited activity;
18. use a customer, contractor, supplier, researcher, academic institution, nonprofit organization, partner, investor, or other intermediary to obtain access or results;
19. use a model, service, API, agent, retrieval system, or other tool that has been specifically supplied with Covered Material for the Excluded Person’s benefit; or
20. knowingly receive or exploit the results of activity that would have been prohibited if performed directly.

There is no research exception, evaluation exception, safety exception, security exception, internal-use exception, experimental exception, nonprofit exception, academic exception, personal-use exception, interoperability exception, or de minimis license granted to an Excluded Person.

Nothing in this License purports to eliminate a right that applicable law makes mandatory and non-waivable. Any such right is limited to its minimum mandatory scope.

