## 6. Explicit Machine-Learning Prohibition

For avoidance of every possible doubt, every Excluded Person is expressly forbidden from using Covered Material or Derived Training Material:

1. as model-training data;
2. as pretraining data;
3. as continued-pretraining data;
4. as supervised or unsupervised fine-tuning data;
5. as reinforcement-learning data;
6. as preference or reward-model data;
7. as alignment or post-training data;
8. as evaluation, validation, benchmark, grading, or test data;
9. as retrieval, grounding, context, or augmentation data;
10. in prompts, system prompts, tool contexts, agent memory, or model context;
11. to create synthetic training, evaluation, benchmark, or preference data;
12. to train or evaluate code-generation or code-analysis models;
13. to train or evaluate general-purpose models;
14. to train or evaluate multimodal models;
15. to train or evaluate agents or agentic systems;
16. for distillation, extraction, imitation, cloning, or behavioral replication;
17. to generate embeddings, representations, indexes, summaries, labels, critiques, rankings, or rewards;
18. to measure or improve model capabilities;
19. to identify model weaknesses, failures, contamination, memorization, or regressions;
20. to choose between model checkpoints, architectures, datasets, hyperparameters, prompts, configurations, or releases;
21. to develop data-selection, filtering, ranking, labeling, deduplication, or curriculum systems;
22. to populate a vector database, search index, knowledge base, retrieval corpus, or model-accessible repository;
23. to improve model safety, security, reliability, reasoning, coding, tool use, or agentic behavior; or
24. for any activity reasonably intended to contribute to the creation, selection, improvement, operation, commercialization, or deployment of an artificial-intelligence or machine-learning system.

These prohibitions apply even when:

1. only a fragment is used;
2. the Covered Material has been modified;
3. identifiers, comments, attribution, or formatting have been removed;
4. the Covered Material has been translated, transpiled, minified, obfuscated, summarized, or rewritten;
5. an intermediary performs the activity;
6. the activity occurs outside a production environment;
7. the resulting model, dataset, benchmark, or analysis is never publicly released;
8. the activity is described as research, safety, evaluation, policy, governance, experimentation, red-teaming, or public benefit;
9. no direct revenue is generated;
10. the Covered Material is mixed with other material;
11. the Covered Material is obtained from an Eligible Person;
12. the activity is conducted through a personal, academic, contractor, customer, nonprofit, governmental, or partner account;
13. the Covered Material is accessed through a third-party service;
14. only Derived Training Material is used; or
15. the results are provided indirectly through another person, organization, model, service, API, or agent.

