## 7. Text-and-Data-Mining Rights Reservation

For purposes of Article 4(3) of Directive (EU) 2019/790 and every implementing, successor, equivalent, or analogous law, the Licensor expressly reserves, in both human-readable and machine-readable form, all rights to reproduce, extract, crawl, scrape, mine, analyze, tokenize, index, embed, transform, or otherwise process Covered Material for text-and-data-mining purposes by or for an Excluded Person.

This reservation covers:

1. all versions and revisions of the Covered Material;
2. repository history;
3. commits, patches, and diffs;
4. documentation and comments;
5. tests and examples;
6. issues, discussions, and associated materials included in the Covered Material;
7. machine-generated representations;
8. Derived Training Material;
9. mirrors, archives, caches, package registries, forks, and third-party copies; and
10. any fragment, transformation, summary, embedding, or representation of the Covered Material.

No text-and-data-mining reservation is made against an Eligible Person. Eligible Persons instead receive the affirmative rights stated in Section 2.

