## 8. Anti-Circumvention and Downstream Preservation

An Eligible Person may not Knowingly:

1. grant or purport to grant an Excluded Person rights in Covered Material;
2. provide Covered Material specifically for use by an Excluded Person;
3. conduct Machine-Learning Activity for an Excluded Person using Covered Material;
4. act as a nominee, proxy, intermediary, data supplier, contractor, purchasing agent, researcher, or service provider to evade this License;
5. create a fork, mirror, package, dataset, service, model, benchmark, index, retrieval system, or derivative work for the purpose of supplying Covered Material or its benefits to an Excluded Person;
6. remove or obscure this License for the purpose of facilitating access by an Excluded Person;
7. permit an Excluded Person to access Covered Material through credentials, infrastructure, repositories, products, or services controlled by the Eligible Person;
8. falsely represent that an Excluded Person is eligible;
9. perform analysis, development, modification, training, evaluation, retrieval, or other work using Covered Material at the request of an Excluded Person;
10. route an Excluded Person’s request through a company, university, nonprofit organization, contractor, agent, family member, trust, foundation, or other intermediary;
11. permit a Permanently Excluded Individual to supervise, direct, approve, participate in, or materially benefit from a project involving Covered Material; or
12. provide an Excluded Person with non-public results materially derived from prohibited access or use.

An Eligible Person has no general duty to investigate, monitor, audit, identify, screen, verify, or report users or customers.

Providing a generally available product or service to the public does not violate this section merely because an unknown Excluded Person accesses it.

Once an Eligible Person has actual knowledge that an Excluded Person is using Covered Material through the Eligible Person’s product, service, account, infrastructure, or organization, the Eligible Person must not knowingly continue enabling that access.

### 8.1 Preservation of the Exclusion

An Eligible Person may license that person’s own modifications and independent additions under any terms.

However, no downstream license, sublicense, contract, package description, repository notice, or other instrument may grant an Excluded Person rights in:

1. the original Covered Material;
2. a substantial portion of the Covered Material; or
3. a derivative work to the extent that it contains the Licensor’s protectable expression.

Every distribution of Covered Material remains subject to Sections 4 through 8, regardless of the license applied to independent modifications.

This requirement does not impose copyleft obligations on independent code merely combined, linked, aggregated, interfaced, or distributed with Covered Material.

---

## 9. Change of Status

If an Eligible Person becomes an Excluded Person:

1. the license granted under Section 2 terminates immediately and prospectively for that person;
2. the person must cease every activity requiring authorization from the Licensor;
3. the person may not continue using copies lawfully obtained before the change of status;
4. the person may not continue using Covered Material through a product, service, model, dataset, benchmark, retrieval system, or development system created before the change of status;
5. the person must cease Machine-Learning Activity involving Covered Material or Derived Training Material; and
6. Sections 4 through 7 apply immediately.

The change of status does not retroactively invalidate acts lawfully performed while the person was eligible.

It prohibits all continued activity requiring authorization after the change.

Rights previously granted to independent Eligible Persons do not terminate merely because another person becomes excluded.

A former member of Excluded Personnel may become eligible after that relationship ends, provided that:

1. the person is not a Permanently Excluded Individual;
2. no other part of the Excluded Person definition applies;
3. the Covered Material is not accessed or used for the benefit of an Excluded Company; and
4. the person obtains a fresh copy through an authorized channel.

### 9.1 No Change of Status for Permanently Excluded Individuals

A Permanently Excluded Individual may not become eligible under this License.

No passage of time, changed circumstances, changed conduct, changed opinion, changed employment, corporate separation, retirement, resignation, dismissal, or dissolution of an Excluded Company creates eligibility.

No rights automatically vest, revive, attach, or become available to a Permanently Excluded Individual.

---

## 10. Termination Applicable to Eligible Persons

An Eligible Person’s rights terminate if that person materially violates a condition of this License.

For an unintentional violation, rights are automatically reinstated if:

1. the violation is cured within thirty days after the person discovers it or receives written notice; and
2. the person takes reasonable measures to prevent recurrence.

No automatic cure or reinstatement applies to:

1. deliberate circumvention;
2. knowing assistance to an Excluded Person;
3. intentional removal, concealment, or falsification of notices;
4. fraudulent concealment of an Excluded Person’s involvement; or
5. repeated violations.

In those cases, reinstatement requires express written authorization from the Licensor.

An Excluded Person has no license capable of termination, cure, or reinstatement unless the Licensor expressly grants that person a separate written license.

### 10.1 No Cure or Reinstatement for Permanently Excluded Individuals

A Permanently Excluded Individual has no public license capable of cure, reinstatement, or restoration.

The cure provisions available to an Eligible Person do not apply to a Permanently Excluded Individual.

A Licensor may grant rights to a Permanently Excluded Individual only through a separate written instrument that:

1. expressly identifies the individual by name;
2. expressly identifies the Covered Material;
3. expressly states that it overrides the permanent exclusion in OAAXL-1.0;
4. states the precise rights granted;
5. is signed by the relevant Licensor; and
6. is delivered directly to the individual or the individual’s authorized legal representative.

A general relicensing, public-license notice, package-registry entry, repository setting, README statement, waiver, failure to enforce, settlement with another person, or publication under another standard form does not by itself waive the permanent exclusion.

No employee, contributor, distributor, sublicensee, hosting provider, package registry, or other third party may waive the exclusion on behalf of the Licensor.

---

## 11. Contractual Access Conditions for Excluded Persons

This section is intended to operate as a contractual access condition in addition to the reservation of intellectual-property rights wherever applicable law recognizes such a contract.

An Excluded Person that intentionally accesses, clones, downloads, obtains, or uses Covered Material after receiving actual notice of this License agrees:

1. not to perform any activity prohibited by this License;
2. immediately to cease unauthorized access and use;
3. to preserve records reasonably necessary to determine the scope of the unauthorized activity;
4. not to destroy evidence after receiving notice of a dispute or claim;
5. upon written demand, to identify repositories, datasets, indexes, retrieval systems, models, checkpoints, adapters, embeddings, services, accounts, and pipelines materially affected by the unauthorized activity;
6. within ten business days after written demand, to certify cessation of the prohibited activity;
